  <h1>Whats Changing in 2025</h1>
  <figure>
    <img src="https://media2.giphy.com/media/v1.Y2lkPTc5MGI3NjExdTc1aTAwOHRic2lteHQybjlsN2s4dmlvcmp6NHR6a3hyaTAycWdkcCZlcD12MV9pbnRlcm5hbF9naWZfYnlfaWQmY3Q9Zw/n2IPMYMthV0m4/giphy.gif" alt="Whats Changing in 2025" width="100" height="100">
    <figcaption>Significant changes to financial regulations in India</figcaption>
  </figure>
  <p>In 2025, there are significant changes coming to <strong>financial regulations in India, particularly starting April 1st</strong>. These include revised income tax slabs, changes to UPI rules, and the launch of the Unified Pension Scheme. Additionally, there are changes to nomination procedures for <em>mutual funds and demat accounts, LPG cylinder prices, and GST regulations</em>. </p>
  <ol>
  <li>Revised tax slabs under the new income tax regime.</li> 
  <li>Changes to UPI rules, likely including increased transaction limits.</li> 
  <li>Changes to GST rules, potentially including mandatory Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) for compliance.</li>
  </ol>
  <h2>Financial Regulations</h2>
  <table border="1" cellpadding="10" cellspacing="0">
    <thead>
      <tr>
          <th>Date</th>
          <th>Regulation</th>
          <th>Details</th>
      </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
      <tr>
          <td>April 17, 2025</td>
          <td>SEBI's Proposal on REITs and InvITs</td>
          <td>SEBI proposed increasing mutual funds' exposure to REITs and InvITs from 10% to 20% to enhance market liquidity and investor participation. Public feedback is being solicited on reclassifying these instruments as equity for index inclusion.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
          <td>April 16, 2025</td>
          <td>Review of ESG Disclosures</td>
          <td>SEBI announced a review of ESG disclosure requirements for listed companies, focusing on supply chain reporting and aiming to simplify compliance, especially for smaller firms.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
          <td>April 15, 2025</td>
          <td>RBI's Securitisation Policy</td>
          <td>The RBI introduced a policy allowing the securitisation of stressed assets, including non-performing loans, to deepen the junk debt market and attract foreign investments.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
          <td>February 1, 2025</td>
          <td>Union Budget 2025-26</td>
          <td>The Finance Minister announced several reforms, including raising FDI limits in insurance to 100%, simplifying KYC processes, and rationalizing ULIP taxation to boost financial inclusion and market participation.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
          <td>October 10, 2023</td>
          <td>Extension of PCA to Government-Owned NBFCs</td>
          <td>The RBI extended the Prompt Corrective Action (PCA) framework to government-owned NBFCs, effective from October 2024, to ensure timely supervisory intervention and maintain financial health.</td>
      </tr>
  </tbody>
  </table>
